<p><b>Cause marketing</b> or <b>cause-related marketing</b> refers to a type of <a href="/wiki/Marketing" title="Marketing">marketing</a> involving the cooperative efforts of a "for profit" business and a <a href="/wiki/Non-profit_organization" title="Non-profit organization">non-profit organization</a> for mutual benefit. The term is sometimes used more broadly and generally to refer to any type of marketing effort for social and other charitable causes, including in-house marketing efforts by non-profit organizations. Cause marketing differs from corporate giving (<a href="/wiki/Philanthropy" title="Philanthropy">philanthropy</a>) as the latter generally involves a specific donation that is <a href="/wiki/Tax_deductible" title="Tax deductible" class="mw-redirect">tax deductible</a>, while cause marketing is a marketing relationship generally not based on a donation.</p>
